<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Edmund" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Edmund:</orth> 1) <cit><quote>E. Langley Duke of York:</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.2.62" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 2, 62</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.85" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.2.15" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 2, 15</bibl>. -- 2) <cit><quote>E. Mortimer Earl of March:</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 2, 36</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.144" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 144</bibl>. -- 3) <cit><quote>son of Roger of March:</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.156" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 156</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.3.26" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.7" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.2.38" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 2, 38</bibl> (confounded by Sh. with Nr. 2). -- 4) <cit><quote>E. duke of Somerset:</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.2.29" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 2, 29</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.9.38" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 9, 38</bibl>. -- 5) the natural son of the Earl of Gloster in <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 25</bibl> etc.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>